    "description": "Vite integration baseline for fast local setup with presets or headless runtime.",
    "content": "\r\n# Vite Integration\r\n\r\nVite is the fastest baseline for local editor iteration.\r\n\r\n## What works\r\n\r\n- Preset editor with CSS import.\r\n- Headless runtime with custom toolbar components.\r\n\r\n## Install\r\n\r\n~~~bash\r\npnpm add @lyfie/luthor\r\n~~~\r\n\r\n~~~tsx\r\nimport '@lyfie/luthor/styles.css';\r\nimport { ExtensiveEditor } from '@lyfie/luthor';\r\n\r\nexport function App() {\r\n  return <ExtensiveEditor placeholder=\"Write here...\" />;\r\n}\r\n~~~\r\n\r\n## Caveats\r\n\r\n- Keep package versions aligned with peer dependency ranges.\r\n- Use the dependencies page to debug duplicated Lexical versions.\r\n\r\n## Related docs\r\n\r\n- [@lyfie/luthor Presets](/docs/luthor/presets/)\r\n- [@lyfie/luthor-headless Overview](/docs/luthor-headless/overview/)\r\n\r\n\r\n",
    "plainContent": "Vite Integration Vite is the fastest baseline for local editor iteration. What works - Preset editor with CSS import. - Headless runtime with custom toolbar components. Install bash pnpm add @lyfie/luthor tsx import '@lyfie/luthor/styles.css'; import { ExtensiveEditor } from '@lyfie/luthor'; export function App() { return ; } Caveats - Keep package versions aligned with peer dependency ranges. - Use the dependencies page to debug duplicated Lexical versions. Related docs - @lyfie/luthor Presets - @lyfie/luthor-headless Overview",
